  <script>
    (window as any).dataLayer = (window as any).dataLayer || [];
    (window as any).gtag = function () {
      (window as any).dataLayer.push(arguments);
    };
    (window as any).gtag("js", new Date());
    (window as any).gtag("config", "G-3TXVE0LR1X");
  </script>
  <title>{pageTitle}</title>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no" />
  <meta
    name="description"
    content="Feed your lawn and control weeds over time with Edwards Landscape Group in Lynchburg, VA."
  />
  <meta
    name="keywords"
    content="fertilization Lynchburg, weed control service, lawn treatment programs, weed prevention"
  />
  <link id="favicon" rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/assets/favicon.ico" />
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Lato:300,400,700&display=swap"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
  <link
    href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Poppins:300,400,500,600,700,800,900"
    rel="stylesheet"
  />
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css"
  />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/animate.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/owl.carousel.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/owl.theme.default.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/magnific-popup.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/ionicons.min.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/flaticon.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/icomoon.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <TopBar />

  <Navigation />
  <main class="service-page service-page--compact">
    <section
      class="service-hero service-hero--trugreen service-hero--compact"
      style="background-image: url('/assets/Fertilization_Service.png');"
    >
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-7 hero-content-block">
            <h1 class="mb-2">Fertilization & Weed Control</h1>
            <h2 class="mb-3">Feed your lawn and control weeds over time.</h2>
            <p class="mb-4 lead">
              A stronger lawn starts with the right nutrients and proactive weed control.
              We tailor treatments to help your grass grow thicker and look better season after season.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get a Free Quote</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row align-items-center gutter-40">
          <div class="col-lg-6">
            <h2 class="mb-3">What’s Included With Fertilization & Weed Control</h2>
            <ul class="checklist">
              <li>Seasonal fertilizer applications</li>
              <li>Weed control targeting common weeds</li>
              <li>Recommendations for mowing and watering</li>
              <li>Optional treatment plans for ongoing improvement</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-lg-6">
            <figure class="service-image-card">
              <img
                src="/assets/Fertilization_Service.png"
                alt="Fertilization treatment applied to a green lawn"
                loading="lazy"
              />
              <figcaption>
                <h3>Seasonal treatments</h3>
                <p>Consistent applications keep lawns dense, green, and weed-resistant.</p>
              </figcaption>
            </figure>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Why Fertilization & Weed Control Matters</h2>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li>Improves color, thickness, and overall lawn health</li>
          <li>Reduces weeds by strengthening turf</li>
          <li>Creates more consistent results across the yard</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">How It Works</h2>
        <ol class="bullet-list">
          <li><strong>Assess:</strong> We look at lawn condition and common weed issues.</li>
          <li><strong>Service:</strong> We apply seasonal treatments and weed control.</li>
          <li><strong>Finish:</strong> We advise on next steps for best results.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Best Time to Schedule</h2>
        <p>Most lawns benefit from a seasonal plan that starts in early spring and continues through fall.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="service-accordion">
          <details open>
            <summary>Will weeds disappear immediately?</summary>
            <p>
            Some weeds respond quickly, but lasting improvement usually happens over multiple treatments.
            Long-term results come from a stronger lawn and consistent control.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Is it safe for pets and kids?</summary>
            <p>
            We’ll provide guidance after application, including when it’s okay to re-enter the lawn.
            Following directions helps ensure safe, effective results.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do you offer one-time treatments?</summary>
            <p>
            Yes, one-time treatments may be available. However, most lawns see the best results with a seasonal plan.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Do I need to water after a treatment?</summary>
            <p>
            It depends on the product and timing. We’ll provide instructions after service so you know what’s best for your lawn.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>Will fertilization burn my lawn?</summary>
            <p>
            When applied correctly, fertilization should not burn your lawn. Proper timing and application rates are important for safe results.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>What weeds do you treat?</summary>
            <p>
            Common weeds vary by season and lawn type. We’ll target the most common issues and adjust based on what we see in your yard.
            </p>
          </details>

          <details>
            <summary>How many treatments do I need per year?</summary>
            <p>
            Many lawns benefit from multiple seasonal treatments. We can recommend a plan based on your lawn goals and existing conditions.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="mb-3">Related Fertilization & Weed Control Articles</h2>
        <ul class="bullet-list">
          <li><a href="/blog/spring-fertilizer-guide-for-virginia-lawns">Spring Fertilizer Guide for Virginia Lawns</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/pre-emergent-vs-post-emergent-weed-control">Pre-Emergent vs. Post-Emergent Weed Control</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/why-weeds-keep-coming-back">Why Weeds Keep Coming Back (And How to Stop Them)</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog/how-to-get-a-thicker-greener-lawn">How to Get a Thicker, Greener Lawn</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="service-section service-section--compact bg-light">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="callout-panel">
          <h2>Get a Free Quote</h2>
          <p>Tell us what you’re seeing (weeds, thin areas, discoloration) and we’ll recommend a plan.</p>
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Request a Free Quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />

  <div id="ftco-loader" class="show fullscreen">
    <svg class="circular" width="48px" height="48px">
      <circle class="path-bg" cx="24" cy="24" r="22" fill="none" stroke-width="4" stroke="#eeeeee"
      ></circle>
      <circle
        class="path"
        cx="24"
        cy="24"
        r="22"
        fill="none"
        stroke-width="4"
        stroke-miterlimit="10"
        stroke="#F96D00"></circle>
    </svg>
  </div>

  <script src="/js/jquery.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery-migrate-3.0.1.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/popper.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/bootstrap.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery.easing.1.3.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery.waypoints.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery.stellar.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/owl.carousel.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/jquery.magnific-popup.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/scrollax.min.js" is:inline></script>
  <script
    src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=AIzaSyBVWaKrjvy3MaE7SQ74_uJiULgl1JY0H2s&sensor=false"
  ></script>
  <script src="/js/google-map.js" is:inline></script>
  <script src="/js/main.js" is:inline></script>
</body>
